{"version":3,"kind":"Article","sha256":"08d82a3e506d9af0c3e350753c18dc655b3b8d60d6b0bbac7b9826b01cb83e4a","slug":"sequencing-2","location":"/metaproteomics/Sequencing.md","dependencies":[],"frontmatter":{"title":"Sequencing","content_includes_title":false,"authors":[{"nameParsed":{"literal":"META-Insight Team","given":"META-Insight","family":"Team"},"name":"META-Insight Team","id":"contributors-myst-generated-uid-0"}],"github":"https://github.com/aababc1/metainsight-book","keywords":["metagenomics","metatranscriptomics","metaproteomics","microbiome","bioinformatics"],"numbering":{"title":{"offset":1}},"source_url":"https://github.com/aababc1/metainsight-book/blob/main/metaproteomics/Sequencing.md","edit_url":"https://github.com/aababc1/metainsight-book/edit/main/metaproteomics/Sequencing.md","thumbnail":"/metainsight-book/build/8d08af7c044f137f7bb82466bad3e9af.png","exports":[{"format":"md","filename":"Sequencing.md","url":"/metainsight-book/build/Sequencing-467e8a5532cab1126226630650a5958e.md"}]},"mdast":{"type":"root","children":[{"type":"block","children":[{"type":"paragraph","position":{"start":{"line":3,"column":1},"end":{"line":3,"column":1}},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"Ribosome profiling (Ribo-seq) is a key technique for translatome analysis, requiring a specialized sample preparation protocol that differs significantly from standard RNA-seq. Rather than capturing total mRNA, this technique isolates ribosome-protected mRNA fragments (ribosome footprints), which represent mRNAs that are actively being translated into proteins at the moment of sample collection. The key steps involve cell lysis under conditions that arrest ribosomes on mRNA (using chloramphenicol), nuclease digestion to degrade unprotected RNA, size-selection of ribosome-bound fragments via gel filtration chromatography, and subsequent library preparation for Illumina sequencing. This chapter provides the complete wet-lab protocol from fecal sample processing through sequencing, with particular attention to the preparation of stock solutions containing translation-arrest reagents and the micrococcal nuclease (MNase) digestion conditions that determine footprint quality ","position":{"start":{"line":3,"column":1},"end":{"line":3,"column":1}},"key":"l6aThgYg3C"},{"type":"cite","url":"doi:10.1126/science.1168978","position":{"start":{"line":3,"column":1},"end":{"line":3,"column":1}},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"Ingolia ","key":"kJMGo6LMx8"},{"type":"emphasis","children":[{"type":"text","value":"et al.","key":"wz1eDiJAzY"}],"key":"ilNJvVVQaz"},{"type":"text","value":" (2009)","key":"HQM0uP8TGU"}],"kind":"narrative","label":"Ingolia_2009","identifier":"doi:10.1126/science.1168978","enumerator":"1","key":"svIlqEcS5e"},{"type":"text","value":".","position":{"start":{"line":3,"column":1},"end":{"line":3,"column":1}},"key":"jLoF4QK8d5"}],"key":"iqXvVeOoDf"},{"type":"heading","depth":2,"position":{"start":{"line":5,"column":1},"end":{"line":5,"column":1}},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"Biological Samples","position":{"start":{"line":5,"column":1},"end":{"line":5,"column":1}},"key":"vmm4fK2eZ2"}],"identifier":"biological-samples","label":"Biological Samples","html_id":"biological-samples","implicit":true,"key":"CQhjBjXqBH"},{"type":"paragraph","position":{"start":{"line":7,"column":1},"end":{"line":7,"column":1}},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"As with metatranscriptomic protocols, immediate RNA stabilization is critical for Ribo-seq. RNAlater preserves the ribosome–mRNA complexes in their native translational state, preventing post-collection changes in ribosome occupancy that would distort the resulting translational profile. Samples must be processed promptly and stored at -80°C to maintain the integrity of ribosome-protected fragments.","position":{"start":{"line":7,"column":1},"end":{"line":7,"column":1}},"key":"BTJWKnzbjf"}],"key":"H2CljQIqqJ"},{"type":"list","ordered":false,"spread":false,"position":{"start":{"line":9,"column":1},"end":{"line":10,"column":1}},"children":[{"type":"listItem","spread":true,"position":{"start":{"line":9,"column":1},"end":{"line":10,"column":1}},"children":[{"type":"paragraph","children":[{"type":"text","value":"Process 500 µL of RNAlater (Ambion) for every 1 g of fecal sample and store it at -80°C","position":{"start":{"line":9,"column":1},"end":{"line":9,"column":1}},"key":"Jtu7f2RRSI"}],"key":"QFRBc9At2C"}],"key":"BlALLfQmnx"}],"key":"XqnPl0Km0E"},{"type":"heading","depth":2,"position":{"start":{"line":11,"column":1},"end":{"line":11,"column":1}},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"Ribosome-bound mRNA prep","position":{"start":{"line":11,"column":1},"end":{"line":11,"column":1}},"key":"yRjzsABJ7F"}],"identifier":"ribosome-bound-mrna-prep","label":"Ribosome-bound mRNA prep","html_id":"ribosome-bound-mrna-prep","implicit":true,"key":"KNKDYgU9hQ"},{"type":"paragraph","position":{"start":{"line":13,"column":1},"end":{"line":13,"column":1}},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"The core of Ribo-seq lies in isolating ribosome-protected mRNA fragments (footprints) of approximately 28–35 nucleotides. This is achieved through a multi-step process: (1) cell lysis in the presence of chloramphenicol to arrest ribosomes at their translational positions, (2) micrococcal nuclease (MNase) digestion to degrade all RNA not physically shielded by a ribosome, and (3) size-selection of monosome-associated fragments via Sephacryl S400 gel filtration columns. The resulting footprints directly correspond to the positions and density of actively translating ribosomes, providing a quantitative readout of protein synthesis that complements but is distinct from total mRNA abundance measured by RNA-seq.","position":{"start":{"line":13,"column":1},"end":{"line":13,"column":1}},"key":"TWxgl8q3nz"}],"key":"OFuD0LI4YA"},{"type":"heading","depth":3,"position":{"start":{"line":15,"column":1},"end":{"line":15,"column":1}},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"Reagents","position":{"start":{"line":15,"col